HEADWORD: Syndyasmian
<hw>Syn`dy*as"mi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>syndyasmo`s</grk> a pairing, fr. <grk>syndya`zein</grk> to
pair.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to the state of pairing together sexually;
-- said of animals during periods of procreation and while rearing their
offspring.</def> <rj><au>Morgan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
